description:
Goodlato launches our new product, "Ugly Sorbets".

Now listen! Approximately 20% of produce or more gets thrown out for cosmetic reasons like weird shapes, odd colors and blemishes. To fight against unnecessary food waste, we partnered with sustainable brands to source these "ugly" berries to turn into tasty and refreshing sorbets, in Goodlato style. Because not only are we committed to making our products low in calorie and low in sugar for a health-driven cause, we are also committed to sustainability, and this will always be in Goodlato's DNA. 

Get the first taste of our Ugly Sorbets on
21st August, 11.30am - 2.30pm at @treatsure pop up at their concept store!

description:
Meet our Rainbow Ice Cream Bread, a co-creation between @microbakerykitchen and Creamier, as our special for the Yong Siak Street Children's Trail happening this Sunday (20th August) along Yong Siak Street.

The bread is freshly crafted by Micro Bakery, and is naturally coloured with Matcha and Sweet Potato Powder for that iconic local rainbow bread look. In line with National Day this August, we paired it with our three heritage flavours - Waffled Putu Piring, Sesame Tang Yuan and Pulut Hitam.

Only available on 20th August at Creamier Tiong Bahru and Micro Bakery, a special for the Yong Siak Street Children's Trail. Don't miss this limited-time delight!

description:
African mahogany, which is commonly known for its deep reddish-brown hues, today exhibits sunkissed, greyish tonesâ€”textures and fissures that indicate the passage of time. Instead of throwing them away, @creamier_sg has embraced the impacts of sunburn and weathering on these benches. Originally designed for the Sultan Gate parklet with URA in 2020, they have since been adopted and housed by Creamier. Leash hooks were later added to the benches at their pet-friendly East Coast outlet.

Thank you for not letting these benches go to waste! + some bonus pics of a wall-bench and ice-cream stools!

description:
@creamier_sg is a local, independent ice cream and lifestyle cafe based in Singapore that has been on its journey since 2011. Partnering with @semula_asia, we worked together to produce an edition of stools for their stores. 

Creamier contributed used and washed Meiji milk bottles, which Semula then transformed into stool tops ornamented with brown swirls that mimic marble streaks. Crafting each stool top required 12 chocolate and 4 coffee bottle caps, along with 42 milk bottles. 

Keeping in line with the theme, we designed the stool legs in reference to ice cream sticks, selecting African Mahoganyâ€™s deep hues to complement and contrast the stool tops.

#rogerandsons #thelocaltreeproject #semulaplastics #creamier #momentsofhappiness

As Singapore celebrates her 58th birthday, Creamier embarks on a culinary dessert journey that pays homage to the rich heritage of our nation.

By preserving the time-honoured flavours that have been cherished by generations of Singaporeans, Creamier hopes to transport patrons back to simpler times and rediscover the magic of local delights as ice creams.

Weâ€™ll be sharing a spotlight on these heritage flavours over the next few weeks:
* Pulut Hitam 
* Sesame Tang Yuan
* Waffled Putu Piring

Check out the new flavours on our online store in the #linkinbio
